Armed Detective Agency The Armed Detective Agency (武 (ぶ)装 (そう)探 (たん)偵 (てい)社 (しゃ),, Busō Tantei-sha?) is an ability user organization. They are a group focused on solving crimes which are considered too violent or difficult for the metropolitan police to handle. Often, these crimes are of a supernatural origin. Nearly all of the detectives within the company have their own special powers known as abilities. item.title: Chalmers Fitzgerald
item.description:
Chalmers Fitzgerald

son of Francis Scott Key and Zelda Fitzgerald
fourth oldest of his family; Eliot's older twin
boy, cis
he/him
gay
starts the series at 7 and ends at 14
born September 26th, 2007
Namesake: Chalmers Archer
Ability: Green Berets
Affiliation: mainly with the Guild Undead first, later on with the Apprentices of the ADA, as well as the ADA itself when the Guild Undead becomes an extended branch of the ADA and the The Gunslinger Kids
Level at which I think about them: low
Brief Notes:
- Chalmers is a timid kid, definitely more so than his younger twin brother, Eliot. In fact, despite being the older one, Eliot is the one who more often takes care of him than the other way around. Definitely was bullied in school, and would've been bullied more had it not been for a combination of Eliot, his big sister Zelda Jr., and of course, his parents (mainly Francis, but Zelda Sr. is also not one to be trifled with when she thinks her babies are being hurt and/or bothered).

item.title: Júlio César (J.C.) Okura-Camarão
item.description:
Júlio César "J.C." Okura-Camarão

son of Teruko (Okura) and Adalcinda Magno (Camarão Luxardo) Okura-Camarão (AKA, Meursault Catgirl)
second oldest of his family, younger twin of Ema
boy, cis (for now)
he/him
technically unknown to him right now, but he's bisexual
starts the series at 3 and ends at 10
born May 6th, 2011
Namesake: Júlio César de Mello e Souza
Ability: The Man Who Counted
Ability Details: No solid idea for him yet, but I want it to deal with numbers somehow. It's not like the unnamed blonde guy's Ability though, but it may be an offensive type Ability, we'll see. Either way, it doesn't play too much importance because the oldest he gets in the actual series is 10 and he never faces any significant danger nor does he truly use his Ability in any of my plans so far.
Affiliation: too young to have one
Level at which I think about them: medium-low, depends on the day sometimes, I like to randomly get soft about Terucinda and their kids sometimes and when I do I think about him
Brief Notes:
A chipper and upbeat little guy, he has a more mellow personality compared to his older twin, Ema, but don't be fooled, he can definitely be a menace when he wants to be, it just so happens that he wants to be a menace less often than his sister. He's Mama-ko's (Teruko) little boy through and through - not to say he doesn't love Mama Cinda, just that he has a favorite and it shows. He and Ema are both close with Nobuo.

item.title: Kazukou Fukuzawa
item.description:
Kazukou Fukuzawa

son of Yukichi & Ougai Fukuzawa
7th oldest of his family; younger twin of Tsuneko
nonbinary demiboy
he/him
pansexual
starts the series at 7 and ends at 14
born February 14th, 2007
Namesake: Kazuko Okakura
Abilities: Book of Tea & All Men Are Equal
Ability Details
Kazukou’s ability, Book of Tea, manifests as a simple hardcover journal with lineless white paper. When the name of a liquid substance is written within it, a cup containing that substance will appear, even if it should not logically be able to be in a cup, or if it would otherwise destroy a container (such as liquid magma). Kazukou can also control the volume and temperature of this liquid, as well as where it will appear and what it will do, by writing those instructions alongside its entry in his journal. While he typically uses this in mundane ways, such as by summoning a hot cup of tea while he’s at school, this definitely has applications that are less benign. He has been known to use it to spill things like salt water and other irritating and/or unsanitary liquids on people he hates, or those who bully his sister.
Kazukou’s secondary ability, All Men Are Equal, was inherited from his father, Yukichi. It works essentially the same way, though instead of only working on subordinates or employees, as Kazukou has no employees, as well as due to his ability being an inherited second generation version of Yukichi’s ability, it only works on those who are able to solve a specific series of puzzles Kazukou puts together specifically for them. Additionally, he will only do this for people he considers himself to be incredibly close with, to the point where he would trust them with his own life.
Affiliation: Armed Detective Agency (major, primary) + Apprentices of the ADA (major, secondary); The Gunslinger Kids (major, primary); The Hawks (major, tertiary)
Level at which I think about them: high. I think about all the fukumorilings so much
Brief Notes:
The eighth-born biological child of Yukichi and Ougai Fukuzawa, Kazukou’s personality is a stark contrast to that of his older twin sister Tsuneko’s. He prefers to be a quiet observer in life, and his general disposition has led many to call him “the family’s Dad (Yukichi) clone.” Their uncanny resemblance to each other is indeed something one tends to notice when meeting one after meeting the other for the first time, and unlike some of his other siblings, Kazukou finds nothing wrong with being compared to his father; in fact, he welcomes it. His quiet demeanor does not at all mean he is a pushover, though, which is a mistake people (specifically, grade school bullies) have made with him before. Kazukou is actually quite the fighter, and coupled with his ability, he definitely has the capability of being deadly, but considering his age, his main goal is simply to get out of most conflicts or end them before they are able to escalate.
Despite his sometimes menacing (even for his age) and stoic appearance, Kazukou is very empathetic, he just tends to show it differently than most people. He is often one of the first people in his family to offer comfort when times are hard, especially if Tsuneko is affected; he knows she is tender-hearted, and is prone to getting very emotional about small things. In order to balance that, he tries to be an emotional rock or anchor, and is prone to taking on big responsibilities a child his age would not normally volunteer to take on and likely shouldn’t. It is often up to his other family members - especially Tsuneko - to remind him of his age, and get him to slow down. He is definitely the type of kid to willingly throw away his own childhood innocence if it meant helping someone else preserve theirs, which makes him a source of worry and concern for his parents.
Kazukou has faced very little great strife in his life, outside of the general difficulties being a child of two of Yokohama’s most powerful men brings, though he has watched his older siblings - namely Junichi, Makoto, and Hyakken - suffer greatly, and has made up his mind to protect Tsuneko and Yoshihiro from as much of that as he can. While he has not yet had to truly put himself in danger for his family, he is definitely willing to. Overall, he is a very sweet boy who inherited all of the protective genes his fathers had to offer, with a strong Resting Autism Face to boot.
